Chilean Stocks: Almendral and Entel Advance; Ripley Retreats

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-11-29T20:43:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/chilean-stocks-almendral-and-entel-advance-ripley-retreats.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index rose 0.1 percent to 4,057.82. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated less than 0.1 percent to 2,174.28.  Empresa Nacional de Telecomunicaciones SA (ENTEL)   rose
1.5 percent to 9,895.9 pesos. Chile’s second-largest mobile
telephone operator announced it would merge with local data,
fixed-line, cable TV and Internet provider Grupo GTD.  Almendral SA (ALMEN)  , Entel’s controller, advanced 3.9
percent to 71 pesos, the steepest gain in 16 weeks.  Ripley Corp SA (RIPLEY)   fell 0.8 percent to 451.74
pesos, its fifth day of losses and its lowest price since Oct.
18. Chile’s third-largest department store operator has
retreated 4.1 percent in the last two days after announcing Nov.
25 third-quarter profit that trailed analysts’ estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  